a) Component Lifecycle in React Functional Components

In functional components, React manages the component lifecycle using the useEffect hook.

1ï¸ Mount Phase

The mount phase occurs when a component is rendered for the first time.

This is represented by:

useEffect(() => {
  // runs once after initial render
}, []);


Common uses: API calls, event listeners, timers.

2ï¸ Update Phase

The update phase occurs whenever specified dependencies change.

This is represented by:

useEffect(() => {
  // runs when dependency value changes
}, [dependency]);


Common uses: reacting to state/prop changes, recalculations.

3ï¸ Unmount Phase

The unmount phase occurs when a component is removed from the DOM.

This is handled using a cleanup function returned from useEffect.

useEffect(() => {
  return () => {
    // cleanup code
  };
}, []);

