b) What is a Cleanup Function? Why Is It Needed?
ðŸ”¹ What is a Cleanup Function?

A cleanup function is a function returned inside useEffect.

It executes before the component unmounts or before the effect runs again.

ðŸ”¹ Why is it Needed?

Cleanup functions are needed to:

Remove event listeners

Clear timers or intervals

Cancel API subscriptions

Prevent memory leaks

Avoid unwanted background processes

ðŸ”¹ Example
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => {
    console.log("Running...");
  }, 1000);

  return () => {
    clearInterval(timer); // cleanup
  };
}, []);